@Node virtualgir

                         @{u}@{b}VirtualGir & GirServer @{ub}@{uu}


   Virtual Gir is a version of the  Gir program, that you  can use from any web browser.
   Gir Server is a server for only one client (more clients next time), basically this
   is simple web-http  server on port 80.

   Why Virtual Gir ?

   Virtual Gir shows the Amiga community, how any program may work from
   just about any web browser without *ctiveX commands, I think it is good idea.
   To do this you have to have a server, in this case GirServer.
   For docs and GirServer SDK you must register your Gir, but
   contact the author first.

   How can I use VirtualGir ?

   First you must start a TCP/IP stack (Amitcp or Miami or ...), then click
   the VirtualGir icon. Don't start GirServer. Then go to any web browser
   and write  the URL:

   http:///index.html (must be "http:///index.html", not "http://index.html"

   that means : http://localhost/index.html (on some browsers this might not work )

   The index.html being the one in Dir GIR05.

   Now a page pops up on your browser, that acts like the GIR05 program itself.
   That is, use this page like the real Gir.

   You can start VirtualGir from any web browser and any computer on the net,
   but you must know the IP address  of the machine, where it is started.
   VirtualGir will only play sound on the Amiga it is started from.

   What is GirServer ?

   It is a http server on port 80. You may use this server for communication with
   a Gir/http client.
    GirServer has a realtime gsm encoder, and a sample  named "speach"
   in same directory as the GirServer will be realtime encoded to the Gir client
   when the client asks for "speach.gsm" from GirServer.

   GirServer will only use the names  "speach.gsm" and "speach" for realtime encoding.
   The  "speach" file must have raw 8 bit, 8 kHz sampling rate format.
   This option will be better documented next time, for now that's all.

   You can put the file help.html in the same directory as the GirServer, if the client
   requests a file, that is not "on" the GirServer domain.

   Anyone that wants more docs and SDK for GirServer system please contact the author.

   @{" Author " Link Author}


